  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Livelihood Opportunities for Youth through IDEJEN</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is designed to improve the economic status and resilience of young people and their families living in deprived areas of Cit&#xE9; Soleil and Martissant. Thanks to ARC&#x2019;s contribution, the project will provide educational and employment opportunities to vulnerable youth out of school in Cit&#xE9; Soleil and Martissant to ensure their socio&#x2013;economic reintegration. The objectives of the project will be to provide basic education, life skills education and technical skills to a group of marginalized out-of-school youth in two Port-au-Prince slums areas during a six month period; reinforce the capacity of 4 Community based organizations located in two slum areas to address programming needs of out-of-school youth in vulnerable situations; provide accompaniment support to out of school youth during a period of six months after the training period in other to find economic opportunities; advocate and develop partnership with the public and private sector to provide economic opportunities to the graduated youth and also to set a task force which could address vulnerable and impoverished youth situation in the rebuilding process of Haiti.</narrative>
  </description>
